PowerShell script to ping a single or multiple computers
This script uses PowerShell to prompt a user to list out a single or multiple computers to be pinged while keeping an active list of 
those which are able to be pinged, and those that are not. It also list all of the relevant infomration like how long it took to ping.

Usage
To use this script, follow these steps:

Open PowerShell by searching for "PowerShell" in the Windows Start Menu or by pressing the Windows key + R and typing "powershell" in the Run dialog box.

Copy and paste the script code into the PowerShell console.

Press Enter to execute the script.

Enter all the computers you'd like to ping (You can also use IP-Addresses) seperated by a comma for multiple computers.

All of the computers and relevant information will be listed.

Press Enter to exit the console window.

Requirements
This script requires Windows PowerShell to be installed on your computer. It should work on any version of Windows that includes PowerShell.
